-- `Die Hard' Director McTiernan Pleads Guilty to Lying in Wiretapping Probe
-- Edvard Pettersson
-- 2010-07-12T22:57:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/-die-hard-director-mctiernan-pleads-guilty-to-lying-in-wiretapping-probe.html

          
          
             “Die Hard” director John
McTiernan, who had been scheduled to go on trial tomorrow for
lying to federal investigators about hiring a private eye to
wiretap a Hollywood producer, has pleaded guilty, said a
spokesman for the U.S. attorney’s office in Los Angeles.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Edvard Pettersson in Los Angeles at 
 epettersson@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        